By Salisu Sani-Idris The National Youth Mandate Group (NYMG) 2023, a pro-democracy organisation, has commended Gov. Yahaya Bello of Kogi state for defeating criminality in the state since the inception of his administration. The National Coordinator of the group, Mr Abba Abba, made the commendation in a statement on Thursday in Abuja. Abba said that the security strategy adopted by Bello has made it impossible for criminals to hibernate in all the nooks and crannies of the state. “There is no gainsaying the fact that Gov. Yahaya Bello of Kogi really understands the crisis of governance in Nigeria. “The governor has demonstrate ability to handle the security situation in his state which was once a home for criminals. “But now as it stands in Nigeria, Kogi remains one of the safest states where one can do business free without fear of losing his or her investment,” Abba said. Abba expressed the hope that Bello has the capacity to consolidate on the gains recorded on security by President Mohammed Buhari because without security, there would be no development. The youth leader called on the leadership of All Progressives Congress (APC) to unanimously endorse Bello and ensure his emergence as the sole candidate of the party in the 2023 General Elections. “The National Youth Mandate Group (NYMG) 2023, advices APC to give their Presidential ticket to Gov. Bello to ensure the emergence of a young president come 2023. “Nigerian Youth will not support any aspirant above 60 years of age hence Bello is best for the ruling party. “Bello is fearless like the lion when its comes to protection of lives, properties and delivering of dividends of democracy.” Abba called on the Nigerian Youth to support one of its own, who has really empowered the youth of his state in all ramifications. “Bello is a detribalized Nigerian who believes in Nigeria and always ready to give his all in the services of humanity. (NAN) (www.nannews.ng)